  </image>
</figure>

          <p>
            The area is maximized when <m>\displaystyle x=\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}</m>.
          </p>
        </li>

      </ol>

        </subsection>
        <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Afterclass36">
          <title>After class</title>
<ol>
        <li>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  In (a), the distance is <m>\sqrt{2000^{2}+600^{2}}\approx 2088</m> feet.
                  At 4 feet per second, this takes 2088/4 = 522 seconds.
                </p>

                <p>
                  In (b), the distance is <m>2000+600=2600</m> feet.
                  It takes <m>2000/6 + 600/4 \approx 483</m> seconds.
                </p>

                <p>
                  In (c), the distance is <m>1000 + \sqrt{1000^{2} + 600^{2}}\approx 2166</m> feet.
                  It takes <m>1000/6 + 1166/4 \approx 458</m> seconds.
                  This is the shortest time.
                </p>
              </li>

              <li>
                <p>
                  Using the fact that time is distance divided by rate, we have
                  <me>
                    T(x) = \frac{x \ {\textrm{ft}}}{6 \ {\textrm{ft/sec}}}+ \frac{ \sqrt{(2000-x)^{2} + 600^{2}} \ {\textrm{ft}} }{4 \ {\textrm{ft/sec}}}= \frac{1}{6}x + \frac{1}{4}\sqrt{4,360,000-4000x+x^{2}}\ {\textrm{seconds}}
                  </me>
                  for <m>0 \leq x \leq 2000</m>.
                </p>
              </li>

              <li>
                <p>
                  The domain of <m>T</m> is <m>[0,2000]</m>.
                  <me>
                    \displaystyle T'(x) = \frac{1}{6}+ \frac{1}{4}\cdot \frac{1}{2}(4,360,000-4000x+x^{2})^{-1/2}(-4000+2x) = 0
                  </me>
                  exactly when <m>x=2000-240\sqrt{5}\approx 1463.34</m> feet.
                  <m>T(1463.34) \approx 445</m> seconds.
                  This is a minimum as shown in <xref ref="AlainaExampleAns"/>.
                </p>
<figure xml:id="AlainaExampleAns">
                <image source="AlainaExamplePic.jpg" width="75%">         
<description>
A graph of a smooth function over x-values from 0 to about 2000. The curve decreases gradually from left to right, then reaches a minimum near the labeled point (1463.34, 445.14). After this point, the graph turns upward slightly, indicating a minimum at that location.
</description>
                </image>
                </figure>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>

